com.mindfusion.scheduling

Class DateStyle

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mindfusion.scheduling.DateStyle

  • public class DateStyle
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines formatting for a range of dates. Can be used either to format either days or months.

      • getPriority

        public int getPriority()
        Description copied from class: DateStyle
        Gets the format priority. If one date has several styles applied to it, only the highest in priority is taken into account.

        When a time cell is included in the time intervals of several DateStyle or DayOfWeekStyle objects, the style that has the highest priority is used.

        Returns:
        An integer value specifying the priority of this style.

      • setPriority

        public void setPriority(int value)
        Description copied from class: DateStyle
        Sets the format priority. If one date has several styles applied to it, only the highest in priority is taken into account.

        When a time cell is included in the time intervals of several DateStyle or DayOfWeekStyle objects, the style that has the highest priority is used.

        Parameters:
        value - An integer value specifying the priority of this style.
